cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.SD, cs.HC 

The paper analyzes the knowledge structure and trends in scientific research in the Online Information Reviews journal, which is related to information retrieval, search engines, the World Wide Web, libraries, and users. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper uses bibliometric and social network analyses, which are related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries). The paper also discusses the evolving discipline of information science, which can be related to cs.SD (Software Development) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
